{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I have a very difficult task."},{"time":3000,"text":"I'm a spectroscopist."},{"time":6000,"text":"I have to talk about astronomy without showing you"},{"time":8000,"text":"any single image of nebulae or galaxies, etc."},{"time":12000,"text":"because my job is spectroscopy."},{"time":14000,"text":"I never deal with images."},{"time":17000,"text":"But I'll try to convince you"},{"time":19000,"text":"that spectroscopy is actually something which can"},{"time":21000,"text":"change this world."},{"time":24000,"text":"Spectroscopy can probably answer the question,"},{"time":27000,"text":"\"Is there anybody out there?\""},{"time":29000,"text":"Are we alone? SETI."},{"time":31000,"text":"It's not very fun to do spectroscopy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":34000,"text":"One of my colleagues in Bulgaria,"},{"time":36000,"text":"Nevena Markova, spent about 20 years"},{"time":38000,"text":"studying these profiles."},{"time":41000,"text":"And she published 42 articles"},{"time":43000,"text":"just dedicated to the subject."},{"time":45000,"text":"Can you imagine? Day and night, thinking,"},{"time":47000,"text":"observing, the same star for 20 years"},{"time":50000,"text":"is incredible."},{"time":52000,"text":"But we are crazy. We do these things."},{"time":54000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":56000,"text":"And I'm not that far."},{"time":58000,"text":"I spent about eight months working on these profiles."},{"time":61000,"text":"Because I've noticed"},{"time":63000,"text":"a very small symmetry"},{"time":65000,"text":"in the profile of one of the planet host stars."},{"time":67000,"text":"And I thought, well maybe there is Lithium-6 in this star,"},{"time":71000,"text":"which is an indication that this star"},{"time":73000,"text":"has swallowed a planet."},{"time":75000,"text":"Because apparently you can't have this fragile isotope"},{"time":78000,"text":"of Lithium-6 in the atmospheres of sun-like stars."},{"time":82000,"text":"But you have it in planets and asteroids."},{"time":85000,"text":"So if you engulf planet or large number of asteroids,"},{"time":91000,"text":"you will have this Lithium-6 isotope"},{"time":94000,"text":"in the spectrum of the star."},{"time":96000,"text":"So I invested more than eight months"},{"time":100000,"text":"just studying the profile of this star."}]},{"cues":[{"time":102000,"text":"And actually it's amazing,"},{"time":104000,"text":"because I got phone calls from many reporters asking,"},{"time":106000,"text":"\"Have you actually seen the planet going into a star?\""},{"time":109000,"text":"Because they thought that if you are having a telescope,"},{"time":113000,"text":"you are an astronomer so what you are doing"},{"time":115000,"text":"is actually looking in a telescope."},{"time":117000,"text":"And you might have seen the planet going into a star."},{"time":121000,"text":"And I was saying, \"No, excuse me."},{"time":123000,"text":"What I see is this one.\""},{"time":125000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":126000,"text":"It's just incredible. Because nobody understood really."},{"time":129000,"text":"I bet that there were very few people"},{"time":131000,"text":"who really understood what I'm talking about."},{"time":134000,"text":"Because this is the indication that the planet went into the star."},{"time":138000,"text":"It's amazing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":141000,"text":"The power of spectroscopy"},{"time":143000,"text":"was actually realized"},{"time":145000,"text":"by Pink Floyd already in 1973."},{"time":149000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":150000,"text":"Because they actually said that"},{"time":153000,"text":"you can get any color you like"},{"time":155000,"text":"in a spectrum."},{"time":157000,"text":"And all you need is time and money"},{"time":159000,"text":"to make your spectrograph."},{"time":161000,"text":"This is the number one high resolution,"},{"time":164000,"text":"most precise spectrograph on this planet, called HARPS,"},{"time":167000,"text":"which is actually used to detect"},{"time":169000,"text":"extrasolar planets and sound waves"},{"time":171000,"text":"in the atmospheres of stars."}]},{"cues":[{"time":173000,"text":"How we get spectra?"},{"time":176000,"text":"I'm sure most of you know from school physics"},{"time":179000,"text":"that it's basically splitting a white light"},{"time":183000,"text":"into colors."},{"time":185000,"text":"And if you have a liquid hot mass,"},{"time":188000,"text":"it will produce something which we call a continuous spectrum."},{"time":192000,"text":"A hot gas is producing emission lines only,"},{"time":195000,"text":"no continuum."},{"time":197000,"text":"And if you place a cool gas in front of a"},{"time":201000,"text":"hot source,"},{"time":203000,"text":"you will see certain patterns"},{"time":205000,"text":"which we call absorption lines."},{"time":207000,"text":"Which is used actually to identify chemical elements"},{"time":210000,"text":"in a cool matter,"},{"time":212000,"text":"which is absorbing exactly at those frequencies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":215000,"text":"Now, what we can do with the spectra?"},{"time":218000,"text":"We can actually study line-of-sight velocities"},{"time":221000,"text":"of cosmic objects."},{"time":223000,"text":"And we can also study chemical composition"},{"time":226000,"text":"and physical parameters of stars,"},{"time":228000,"text":"galaxies, nebulae."},{"time":230000,"text":"A star is the most simple object."},{"time":232000,"text":"In the core, we have thermonuclear reactions going on,"},{"time":236000,"text":"creating chemical elements."},{"time":238000,"text":"And we have a cool atmosphere."},{"time":240000,"text":"It's cool for me."},{"time":242000,"text":"Cool in my terms is three or four or five thousand degrees."},{"time":246000,"text":"My colleagues in infra-red astronomy"},{"time":248000,"text":"call minus 200 Kelvin is cool for them."},{"time":253000,"text":"But you know, everything is relative."},{"time":255000,"text":"So for me 5,000 degrees is pretty cool."},{"time":258000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":259000,"text":"This is the spectrum of the Sun --"},{"time":262000,"text":"24,000 spectral lines,"},{"time":265000,"text":"and about 15 percent of these lines is not yet identified."},{"time":269000,"text":"It is amazing. So we are in the 21st century,"},{"time":272000,"text":"and we still cannot properly understand"},{"time":274000,"text":"the spectrum of the sun."},{"time":276000,"text":"Sometimes we have to deal with"},{"time":278000,"text":"just one tiny, weak spectral line"},{"time":281000,"text":"to measure the composition of that chemical element in the atmosphere."},{"time":285000,"text":"For instance, you see the spectral line of the gold"},{"time":288000,"text":"is the only spectral line in the spectrum of the Sun."},{"time":291000,"text":"And we use this weak feature"},{"time":293000,"text":"to measure the composition"},{"time":295000,"text":"of gold in the atmosphere of the Sun."}]},{"cues":[{"time":298000,"text":"And now this is a work in progress."},{"time":301000,"text":"We have been dealing with a similarly very weak feature,"},{"time":305000,"text":"which belongs to osmium."},{"time":307000,"text":"It's a heavy element produced in thermonuclear"},{"time":311000,"text":"explosions of supernovae."},{"time":313000,"text":"It's the only place where you can produce, actually, osmium."},{"time":316000,"text":"Just comparing the composition of osmium"},{"time":320000,"text":"in one of the planet host stars,"},{"time":322000,"text":"we want to understand why there is so much"},{"time":324000,"text":"of this element."},{"time":326000,"text":"Perhaps we even think that maybe"},{"time":329000,"text":"supernova explosions trigger formations of planets and stars."},{"time":333000,"text":"It can be an indication."}]},{"cues":[{"time":336000,"text":"The other day, my colleague from Berkeley,"},{"time":338000,"text":"Gibor Basri, emailed me"},{"time":340000,"text":"a very interesting spectrum,"},{"time":342000,"text":"asking me, \"Can you have a look at this?\""},{"time":344000,"text":"And I couldn't sleep, next two weeks,"},{"time":348000,"text":"when I saw the huge amount of oxygen"},{"time":351000,"text":"and other elements in the spectrum of the stars."},{"time":353000,"text":"I knew that there is nothing like that observed in the galaxy."},{"time":357000,"text":"It was incredible. The only conclusion we could make from this"},{"time":361000,"text":"is clear evidence that there was a supernova explosion"},{"time":364000,"text":"in this system, which polluted the atmosphere"},{"time":367000,"text":"of this star."},{"time":369000,"text":"And later a black hole was formed"},{"time":371000,"text":"in a binary system,"},{"time":373000,"text":"which is still there with a mass of about"},{"time":375000,"text":"five solar masses."},{"time":377000,"text":"This was considered as first evidence that actually black holes"},{"time":380000,"text":"come from supernovae explosions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":384000,"text":"My colleagues, comparing composition of chemical elements"},{"time":386000,"text":"in different galactic stars,"},{"time":388000,"text":"actually discovered alien stars in our galaxy."},{"time":392000,"text":"It's amazing that you can go so far"},{"time":395000,"text":"simply studying the chemical composition of stars."},{"time":399000,"text":"They actually said that one of the stars you see in the spectra"},{"time":402000,"text":"is an alien. It comes from a different galaxy."},{"time":405000,"text":"There is interaction of galaxies. We know this."},{"time":408000,"text":"And sometimes they just capture stars."}]},{"cues":[{"time":413000,"text":"You've heard about solar flares."},{"time":416000,"text":"We were very surprised to discover"},{"time":418000,"text":"a super flare,"},{"time":420000,"text":"a flare which is thousands of millions of times"},{"time":424000,"text":"more powerful than those we see in the Sun."},{"time":426000,"text":"In one of the binary stars in our galaxy"},{"time":429000,"text":"called FH Leo,"},{"time":431000,"text":"we discovered the super flare."},{"time":433000,"text":"And later we went to study the spectral stars"},{"time":437000,"text":"to see is there anything strange with these objects."},{"time":439000,"text":"And we found that everything is normal."},{"time":442000,"text":"These stars are normal like the Sun. Age, everything was normal."},{"time":445000,"text":"So this is a mystery."},{"time":447000,"text":"It's one of the mysteries we still have, super flares."},{"time":450000,"text":"And there are six or seven similar cases"},{"time":453000,"text":"reported in the literature."}]},{"cues":[{"time":455000,"text":"Now to go ahead with this,"},{"time":457000,"text":"we really need to understand chemical evolution of the universe."},{"time":461000,"text":"It's very complicated. I don't really want you to"},{"time":463000,"text":"try to understand what is here."},{"time":467000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":468000,"text":"But it's to show you how complicated is the whole story"},{"time":471000,"text":"of the production of chemical elements."},{"time":473000,"text":"You have two channels --"},{"time":475000,"text":"the massive stars and low-mass stars --"},{"time":477000,"text":"producing and recycling matter and chemical elements in the universe."},{"time":480000,"text":"And doing this for 14 billion years,"},{"time":483000,"text":"we end up with this picture,"},{"time":485000,"text":"which is a very important graph,"},{"time":487000,"text":"showing relative abundances of chemical elements"},{"time":490000,"text":"in sun-like stars"},{"time":492000,"text":"and in the interstellar medium."}]},{"cues":[{"time":495000,"text":"So which means that it's really impossible"},{"time":497000,"text":"to find an object where you find about 10 times more sulfur than silicon,"},{"time":502000,"text":"five times more calcium than oxygen. It's just impossible."},{"time":506000,"text":"And if you find one, I will say that"},{"time":508000,"text":"this is something related to SETI,"},{"time":511000,"text":"because naturally you can't do it."},{"time":515000,"text":"Doppler Effect is something very important"},{"time":517000,"text":"from fundamental physics."},{"time":519000,"text":"And this is related to the change of the frequency"},{"time":521000,"text":"of a moving source."},{"time":523000,"text":"The Doppler Effect is used to discover extrasolar planets."}]},{"cues":[{"time":528000,"text":"The precision which we need"},{"time":530000,"text":"to discover a Jupiter-like planet"},{"time":532000,"text":"around a sun-like star"},{"time":534000,"text":"is something like 28.4 meters per second."},{"time":538000,"text":"And we need nine centimeters per second"},{"time":540000,"text":"to detect an Earth-like planet."},{"time":543000,"text":"This can be done with the future spectrographs."},{"time":546000,"text":"I, myself, I'm actually involved in the team"},{"time":550000,"text":"which is developing a CODEX,"},{"time":552000,"text":"high resolution, future generation spectrograph"},{"time":554000,"text":"for the 42 meter E-ELT telescope."},{"time":558000,"text":"And this is going to be an instrument"},{"time":561000,"text":"to detect Earth-like planets"},{"time":563000,"text":"around sun-like stars."},{"time":565000,"text":"It is an amazing tool called astroseismology"},{"time":568000,"text":"where we can detect sound waves"},{"time":571000,"text":"in the atmospheres of stars."}]},{"cues":[{"time":573000,"text":"This is the sound of an Alpha Cen."},{"time":576000,"text":"We can detect sound waves"},{"time":578000,"text":"in the atmospheres of sun-like stars."},{"time":580000,"text":"Those waves have frequencies"},{"time":583000,"text":"in infrasound domain, the sound actually nobody knows, domain."},{"time":587000,"text":"Coming back to the most important question,"},{"time":589000,"text":"\"Is there anybody out there?\""},{"time":591000,"text":"This is closely related"},{"time":593000,"text":"to tectonic and volcanic activity of planets."},{"time":597000,"text":"Connection between life"},{"time":599000,"text":"and radioactive nuclei"},{"time":601000,"text":"is straightforward."},{"time":603000,"text":"No life without tectonic activity,"},{"time":606000,"text":"without volcanic activity."},{"time":608000,"text":"And we know very well that geothermal energy"},{"time":610000,"text":"is mostly produced by decay of uranium, thorium, and potassium."}]},{"cues":[{"time":615000,"text":"How to measure, if we have planets"},{"time":619000,"text":"where the amount of those elements is small,"},{"time":623000,"text":"so those planets are tectonically dead,"},{"time":626000,"text":"there cannot be life."},{"time":628000,"text":"If there is too much uranium or potassium or thorium,"},{"time":631000,"text":"probably, again, there would be no life."},{"time":634000,"text":"Because can you imagine everything boiling?"},{"time":636000,"text":"It's too much energy on a planet."},{"time":638000,"text":"Now, we have been measuring abundance"},{"time":640000,"text":"of thorium in one of the stars with extrasolar planets."},{"time":644000,"text":"It's exactly the same game. A very tiny feature."}]},{"cues":[{"time":648000,"text":"We are actually trying to measure this profile"},{"time":650000,"text":"and to detect thorium."},{"time":652000,"text":"It's very tough. It's very tough."},{"time":654000,"text":"And you have to, first you have to convince yourself."},{"time":656000,"text":"Then you have to convince your colleagues."},{"time":658000,"text":"And then you have to convince the whole world"},{"time":661000,"text":"that you have actually detected something like this"},{"time":664000,"text":"in the atmosphere of an extrasolar planet"},{"time":666000,"text":"host star somewhere in 100 parsec away from here."},{"time":669000,"text":"It's really difficult."},{"time":671000,"text":"But if you want to know about a life on extrasolar planets,"},{"time":676000,"text":"you have to do this job."},{"time":678000,"text":"Because you have to know how much of radioactive element you have"},{"time":681000,"text":"in those systems."}]},{"cues":[{"time":683000,"text":"The one way to discover about aliens"},{"time":686000,"text":"is to tune your radio telescope and listen to the signals."},{"time":690000,"text":"If you receive something interesting,"},{"time":693000,"text":"well that's what SETI does actually,"},{"time":695000,"text":"what SETI has been doing for many years."},{"time":698000,"text":"I think the most promising way"},{"time":700000,"text":"is to go for biomarkers."},{"time":703000,"text":"You can see the spectrum of the Earth, this Earthshine spectrum,"},{"time":706000,"text":"and that is a very clear signal."},{"time":709000,"text":"The slope which is coming, which we call a Red Edge,"},{"time":712000,"text":"is a detection of vegetated area."},{"time":716000,"text":"It's amazing that we can detect vegetation"},{"time":720000,"text":"from a spectrum."},{"time":722000,"text":"Now imagine doing this test"},{"time":724000,"text":"for other planets."}]},{"cues":[{"time":727000,"text":"Now very recently, very recently,"},{"time":730000,"text":"I'm talking about last six, seven, eight months,"},{"time":733000,"text":"water, methane, carbon dioxide"},{"time":737000,"text":"have been detected in the spectrum"},{"time":739000,"text":"of a planet outside the solar system."},{"time":742000,"text":"It's amazing. So this is the power of spectroscopy."},{"time":746000,"text":"You can actually go and detect"},{"time":749000,"text":"and study a chemical composition of planets"},{"time":752000,"text":"far, far, far from solar system."},{"time":755000,"text":"We have to detect oxygen or ozone"},{"time":758000,"text":"to make sure that we have all necessary conditions"},{"time":761000,"text":"to have life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":765000,"text":"Cosmic miracles are something"},{"time":767000,"text":"which can be related to SETI."},{"time":769000,"text":"Now imagine an object, amazing object,"},{"time":771000,"text":"or something which we cannot explain"},{"time":773000,"text":"when we just stand up and say,"},{"time":775000,"text":"\"Look, we give up. Physics doesn't work.\""},{"time":777000,"text":"So it's something which you can always refer to SETI and say,"},{"time":780000,"text":"\"Well, somebody must be doing this, somehow.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":785000,"text":"And with the known physics etc,"},{"time":787000,"text":"it's something actually which has been pointed out"},{"time":789000,"text":"by Frank Drake,"},{"time":791000,"text":"many years ago, and Shklovsky."},{"time":793000,"text":"If you see, in the spectrum of a planet host star,"},{"time":796000,"text":"if you see strange chemical elements,"},{"time":800000,"text":"it can be a signal from a civilization"},{"time":803000,"text":"which is there and they want to signal about it."},{"time":806000,"text":"They want to actually signal their presence"},{"time":810000,"text":"through these spectral lines,"},{"time":812000,"text":"in the spectrum of a star, in different ways."}]},{"cues":[{"time":815000,"text":"There can be different ways doing this."},{"time":817000,"text":"One is, for instance, technetium"},{"time":819000,"text":"is a radioactive element"},{"time":821000,"text":"with a decay time of 4.2 million years."},{"time":824000,"text":"If you suddenly observe technetium"},{"time":827000,"text":"in a sun-like star,"},{"time":829000,"text":"you can be sure that somebody has put this"},{"time":831000,"text":"element in the atmosphere,"},{"time":833000,"text":"because in a natural way it is impossible to do this."},{"time":837000,"text":"Now we are reviewing the spectra of about"},{"time":840000,"text":"300 stars with extrasolar planets."},{"time":843000,"text":"And we are doing this job since 2000"},{"time":847000,"text":"and it's a very heavy project."},{"time":850000,"text":"We have been working very hard."},{"time":852000,"text":"And we have some interesting cases,"},{"time":856000,"text":"candidates, so on, things which we can't really explain."},{"time":860000,"text":"And I hope in the near future"},{"time":863000,"text":"we can confirm this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":865000,"text":"So the main question: \"Are we alone?\""},{"time":867000,"text":"I think it will not come from UFOs."},{"time":870000,"text":"It will not come from radio signals."},{"time":874000,"text":"I think it will come from a spectrum like this."},{"time":878000,"text":"It is the spectrum of a planet like Earth,"},{"time":883000,"text":"showing a presence of nitrogen dioxide,"},{"time":886000,"text":"as a clear signal of life,"},{"time":889000,"text":"and oxygen and ozone."},{"time":891000,"text":"If, one day, and I think it will be"},{"time":893000,"text":"within 15 years from now, or 20 years."},{"time":896000,"text":"If we discover a spectrum like this"},{"time":899000,"text":"we can be sure that there is life on that planet."},{"time":901000,"text":"In about five years we will discover"},{"time":904000,"text":"planets like Earth, around sun-like stars,"},{"time":907000,"text":"the same distance as the Earth from the Sun."},{"time":910000,"text":"It will take about five years."},{"time":912000,"text":"And then we will need another 10, 15 years"},{"time":914000,"text":"with space projects"},{"time":916000,"text":"to get the spectra of Earth-like planets like the one I showed you."},{"time":919000,"text":"And if we see the nitrogen dioxide"},{"time":921000,"text":"and oxygen,"},{"time":923000,"text":"I think we have the perfect E.T."},{"time":925000,"text":"Thank you very much."},{"time":927000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}